subject: RE: [Read_Alphabet] Re: Posted Lord's Prayer GIF
msgSnippet: Hi All, From how I pronounce it, I d go with this: 3-25-28-11-1-30-11-28-11 trespAses cak pek _____ From: mcbroom1946 [mailto:mcbroom1946@yahoo.com] Sent:
messageBody:
Hi All,
 
From how I pronounce it, I'd go with this:
 
3-25-28-11-1-30-11-28-11

trespAses

 

cak pek

From: mcbroom1946 [mailto:mcbroom1946@...]
Sent: Wednesday, September 01, 2004 1:50 PM
To: Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [Read_Alphabet] Re: Posted Lord's Prayer GIF

I think what you have found is an inversion - the writer is trying to express the
last syllable -es, but got the letters backwards.

Personally, I would have used 28-12, however.



--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, delrayva@y... wrote:
> There seems to be an error in the Lord's Prayer GIF posted on
this
> site.  The word "Trespasses" seems to have an extra #36 at
the end of
> it.
>
> It reads as
3-25-28-11-1-30-11-12-36
> When 3-25-28-11-1-30-11-12 seems
sufficient.
>
> Is my assessment correct?
>
>
Thanks,
> DelRayVA
